            "text": " **Fact 1.** Let  $\\mathcal{A}$  be a PFA and  $\\mathcal{P}(\\mathcal{A})$  be its power automaton. Then  $\\mathcal{A}$  is carefully synchronizing if and only if for some state  $q \\in Q$  there exists a path in  $\\mathcal{P}(\\mathcal{A})$  from Q to  $\\{q\\}$ . The shortest synchronizing word for A corresponds to the shortest such path in  $\\mathcal{P}(\\mathcal{A})$ .",
